OL,6,FFormer politician Lindsay Ash, who
OL,7,Fused to be involved in planning
OL,8,Fdecisions, comments: "We can't go
OL,9,Fback, we have to push on, people
OL,10,Fshould not look at this as a victory
OL,11,Fbut as an absolute disaster and
OL,12,Fprobably the most costly in the
OL,13,Fhistory of Jersey's finance."
OL,15,FDevelopment works are due to start
OL,16,Fthis spring with the area prepared for
OL,17,Fwork as site hoardings and welfare
OL,18,Ffacilities are installed, alongside
OL,19,Fthe removal of topsoil and redundant
OL,20,Futilities - a main contractor also
OL,21,Fneeds to be chosen.
